    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-11-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="573"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord
                        Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-11-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 16, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Lord Lyons:</hi> Your letters of the respective
                    dates of’the 12th and 13th instant, apprising me of the prompt proceedings of
                    his excellency Viscount Monck in regard to the Georgiana, were duly and
                    thankfully received. Believe me to be, my dear Lord Lyons, always and faithfully
                    yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
